                <h3>Work Permit process for Netherland</h3>
                <h4>Project details:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Project Name: ING - MAPI_Y Code</li>
                    <li>Project Y Code: Y/150507</li>
                </ul>
                <h5>Keep the below documents ready to initiate your Netherland work permit:</h5>
                <ul class="permit-list">
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Copy of Deputation Letter signed by both Employer and Employee (HR to provide) (Refer How to raise TMS request? Section for more detail)</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Clear copy of Pre-Departure Induction Completion Certificate (Upload Certificate only) - Onsite Travelers have to attend the Pre-Departure Orientation Session to receive the Pre-Departure Induction Completion Certificate. The schedule, meeting id, dial in numbers for the same are provided in the link: <a href="https://meme.hcl.com/?destination=pages/388118/page-tab/393057" target="_blank">https://meme.hcl.com/pages/388118/page-tab/393057</a></li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Signed "To Whom it may concern Letter" on HCL India Letterhead
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Certificate of Coverage Acknowledgement received from the PF team (Refer How to raise CoC certificate? Section for more detail)
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Scanned copy of Graduate & PG Degree Certificate along with Mark Sheets
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Scanned copy of Passport all 36 pages in one PDF (Clear Color Copy)
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>	Resume in HCL Format
                </ul>

                <h5>There are four steps you should follow to complete the VISA process</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>1.	Raise TMS request and get the deputation letter from HR</li>
                    <li>2.	Raise CoC (Certificate of Coverage</li>
                    <li>3.	Raise GIS request and get the appointment from Embassy</li>
                    <li>4.	Raise request for Visa Stamping</li>
                </ul>
                @*<p><strong>Note:</strong> You can do the first two process in parallel than raise GIS request.</p>*@
                <p class="note">
                    <span class="underline">Note:</span>  COC is <span class="underline red">not</span> mandatory for GIS. Please upload the PDF that got generated when you filled in the application form. COC can proceed in parallel to WP.
                    Please submit your GIS application as soon as TMS letter is released
                </p>
                <br>
                <h5>1.	How to raise TMS request?</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Go to MyHCL and open TMS from search option</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Click on "Initiate Visa" and select country as Netherland and other details as mentioned below</li>
                    <li><img src="~/Images/img-2.png" alt="" /></li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Client Address: ING Bank, Amsterdamse Poort, Bijlmerplein 888 1102 MG Amsterdam</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> In the upload section, upload the approval email which you got from your AM/DU Head and submit</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> This will take a couple weeks to issue the deputation letter</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>2.	How to Raise CoC certificate?</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Go to MyHCL and open My Profile (ESS) from search option</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Under My Information - Personal section select the last option which is "Certificate of Coverage"</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Click Add new CoC button</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Select the country as Netherland and fill your personal details</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> You can get your Pension Number from your HCL payslip</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> In Employer (India) section select HCL Technologies Ltd and other details would have filled up automatically</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Under Employer Place of Work in Netherlands select Name as HCL Technologies B.V</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Address: Prinses Margrietplantsoen 50, 9th Floor - Unit 9.02 / E Tower, 2595 BR, Den Hague, Netherlands</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> CoC From and To Date: Get it from your RM/PM</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Place of Work: Netherlands </li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Cross verify once again and press Submit</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Once submitted it will go for an approval and after the request got approved you will get an Email from helpdesk team to file your CoC request in Government of India web portal along with RM duly filled RM declaration form.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Pls follow the instructions mentioned on the Certificate of Coverage process document</li>
                    <li>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/Certificate of Coverage Process.docx">Certificate of Coverage Process</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/COC Online Application.docx">COC Online application</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/RM Declaration Form.doc">RM Declaration Form</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Sample COC online application screenshot doc is FYR</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Login to ePFO site and submit the details as described in the above document</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Once details got submitted in the web portal it will generate an PDF file which you need download and keep it safe</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Again you need to duly sign on the CoC letter generated from ePFO site, scan and upload it back to your CoC application request which you raised on HCL-ESS-CoC form</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> This is very important without re uploading the signed CoC letter the helpdesk will not close your CoC request</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Next, take print out of the RM declaration form, fill all the details manually, get it signed by your RM and send the original hard copy to the Helpdesk team</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> This process will take up to a month time to get it attested by government of India, post that you will get your approved CoC letter which again you need to keep it safe</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>3. How to raise GIS request?</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Go to MyHCL and open Global Immigration Solutions (GIS) from search option</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> click on initiate and select the respective country</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Make sure that your personal details are correct and your RM and project is well updated</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Also fill the passport details and make sure its updated in ESS</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Fill your travel dates along with project code and other details mentioned below</li>
                    <li><img src="~/Images/img-2.png" alt="" /></li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Under document upload section read all details carefully and submit all the supporting documents</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Copy of Deputation Letter signed by both Employer and Employee (HR to provide)</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Clear copy of Pre-Departure Induction Completion Certificate (Upload Certificate only) – Onsite Travelers have to attend the Pre-Departure Orientation Session to receive the Pre-Departure Induction Completion Certificate. The schedule, meeting id, dial in numbers for the same are provided in the link: <a href="https://meme.hcl.com/?destination=pages/388118/page-tab/393057" target="_blank">https://meme.hcl.com/pages/388118/page-tab/393057</a></li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Signed "To Whom it may concern Letter" on HCL India Letterhead</li>
                    <li>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Data.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Data</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Java.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Java</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - PEGA.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - PEGA</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Testing.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Testing</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Tribe.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - Tribe</a></li>
                            <li><i class="fa fa-file-word-o" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="~/NL Work Permit/To Whom So Ever It May Concern - UI Devolopment.doc">To Whom So Ever It May Concern - UI Devolopment</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Certificate of Coverage Acknowledgement received from the PF team</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Graduate & PG Degree Certificate along with Mark Sheets</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Passport all 36 pages in one PDF (Clear Color Copy)</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Resume in HCL Format</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Mentioned down the list of supporting documents</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Once you submit the DOC your RM will approve.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> After RM approval it goes to ISG which approves and raise request in 3 days.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Once ISG submits it to Embassy you will receive mail with control number.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> After 13-14 working days you need to check the status of your decision with provided control number online at mention link given in mail.</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Post approval you will get a confirmation email from Helpdesk team than you need to raise Visa Stamping request for BIOMETRIC and VISA Stamping</li>
                </ul>
                <h5>4. How to raise VISA Stamping request?</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Go to MyHCL and open Global Immigration Solutions (GIS) from search option</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> click on initiate and select "VISA Stamping"</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Make sure that your personal details are correct and your RM and project is well updated and submit</li>
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Post its get approved you will get a confirmation email from Helpdesk team to fill up the MVV forms and submit
                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> Once all are verified, team will ask you to come and collet the MVV application form and cover letters. After collecting the document, the helpdesk team will book an appointment with Netherland embassy</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Once you done with all, please raise a TAS and make sure you raise a TAS 5 day's prior your appointment date in Netherland Embassy.</p>
                <p>Be on time at embassy and surrender your passport for VISA stamping. VISA stamping will be done in a day and you can collect your passport by going to Embassy in person on very next day.</p>
                <p>If the urgency is high, stay overnight in Delhi and collect your passport from embassy on very next day if not there is an "Authority letter" which you need to sign and handover to the local HCL vendor partner and they will go and collect it on behalf of you and courier to your respective HCL premises.</p>
                <p><strong>Note:</strong> Please make sure you take the print out of Authority letter and get the contact person details from helpdesk team before you travel</p>
                <p>Once helpdesk team got your passport will intimate you than you can go and collect your passport</p>


            </div>

